>
  <article class="blog-post">
    <header class="post-header">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> / 
          <a href="/blog/">Blog</a> / 
          <span>Budget-Friendly Date Night</span>
        </div>
        
        <h1>Budget-Friendly Date Night Restaurants in Los Angeles: Romantic Dining Under $50</h1>
        
        <div class="post-meta">
          <time datetime="2024-01-15">January 15, 2024</time>
          <span class="author">by Date Night Experts</span>
          <span class="category">Budget Dining</span>
        </div>
        
        <div class="post-excerpt">
          <p>Romantic date nights don't have to break the bank. Discover LA's best budget-friendly restaurants that offer incredible food, romantic ambiance, and memorable experiences for under $50 per person.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="post-content">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="content-wrapper">
          <div class="main-content">
            <section class="intro-section">
              <h2>Why Budget-Friendly Doesn't Mean Compromising on Romance</h2>
              <p>Los Angeles is home to countless hidden gems that offer incredible dining experiences without the hefty price tag. From cozy neighborhood bistros to trendy cafes with romantic ambiance, you can enjoy memorable date nights while staying within your budget.</p>
              
              <p>Many of LA's most romantic restaurants focus on fresh, local ingredients and creative presentations that rival their more expensive counterparts. The key is knowing where to look and what to order to maximize your dining experience while keeping costs reasonable.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="restaurants-section">
              <h2>Best Budget-Friendly Date Night Restaurants in LA</h2>
              
              {budgetRestaurants.slice(0, 10).map((restaurant, index) => (
                <div class="restaurant-feature">
                  <div class="restaurant-header">
                    <h3>{index + 1}. {restaurant.name}</h3>
                    <div class="restaurant-rating">
                      <div class="stars">‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ</div>
                      <span class="rating">{restaurant.rating}/5</span>
                      <span class="date-score">Date Score: {restaurant.dateNightScore}</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  
                  <div class="restaurant-details">
                    <p class="restaurant-description">
                      {restaurant.description || `Experience exceptional ${restaurant.cuisineTypes.join(', ')} cuisine in a romantic setting perfect for budget-conscious date nights. Great value with excellent food and ambiance.`}
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="restaurant-info">
                      <div class="info-item">
                        <strong>Address:</strong> {restaurant.address}
                      </div>
                      <div class="info-item">
                        <strong>Phone:</strong> {restaurant.phone}
                      </div>
                      <div class="info-item">
                        <strong>Price Level:</strong> {'$'.repeat(restaurant.priceLevel)}
                      </div>
                      <div class="info-item">
                        <strong>Cuisine:</strong> {restaurant.cuisineTypes.join(', ')}
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="budget-tips">
                      <h4>üí∞ Budget-Friendly Tips:</h4>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Share appetizers and desserts</li>
                        <li>Look for happy hour specials</li>
                        <li>Order house wines or cocktails</li>
                        <li>Consider lunch instead of dinner</li>
                        <li>Check for weekday specials</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="restaurant-actions">
                      <a href={`/losangeles/${restaurant.slug}/`} class="btn btn-primary">View Restaurant Details</a>
                      {restaurant.website && (
                        <a href={restaurant.website} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-secondary">Make Reservation</a>
                      )}
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              ))}
