                  <ul>
                    <li>Classic Italian cuisine</li>
                    <li>Generous portions</li>
                    <li>Romantic ambiance</li>
                    <li>Family-style dining</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="neighborhood-card">
                  <h3>üå∂Ô∏è Thai Town</h3>
                  <p>Authentic Thai cuisine with bold flavors and reasonable prices. Many restaurants offer lunch specials and early bird deals.</p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Authentic Thai flavors</li>
                    <li>Lunch specials</li>
                    <li>Spicy and mild options</li>
                    <li>Vegetarian-friendly</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="budget-tips">
              <h2>Money-Saving Date Night Tips</h2>
              
              <div class="tips-grid">
                <div class="tip-card">
                  <h3>üì± Use Apps and Coupons</h3>
                  <p>Check Groupon, Restaurant.com, and restaurant apps for deals and discounts. Many restaurants offer first-time customer discounts.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tip-card">
                  <h3>üç∑ BYOB Options</h3>
                  <p>Look for restaurants that allow you to bring your own wine. This can save $20-40 on your bill while still enjoying a romantic dinner.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tip-card">
                  <h3>üåÆ Street Food Adventures</h3>
                  <p>Explore LA's food truck scene and street food markets. You can try multiple cuisines and dishes for a fraction of restaurant prices.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tip-card">
                  <h3>‚òï Coffee Shop Dates</h3>
                  <p>Many coffee shops offer light meals, pastries, and romantic ambiance. Perfect for casual date nights with great atmosphere.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="budget-menu-guide">
              <h2>Budget-Friendly Menu Guide</h2>
              
              <div class="menu-sections">
                <div class="menu-section">
                  <h3>ü•ó Appetizers Under $15</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li><strong>Bruschetta:</strong> Fresh tomatoes, basil, and garlic on toasted bread</li>
                    <li><strong>Hummus Plate:</strong> House-made hummus with pita and vegetables</li>
                    <li><strong>Spring Rolls:</strong> Fresh vegetables wrapped in rice paper</li>
                    <li><strong>Nachos:</strong> Loaded with beans, cheese, and fresh toppings</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="menu-section">
                  <h3>üçù Main Courses Under $25</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li><strong>Pasta Dishes:</strong> Fresh pasta with seasonal ingredients</li>
                    <li><strong>Pizza:</strong> Wood-fired or traditional style with quality toppings</li>
                    <li><strong>Rice Bowls:</strong> Asian-inspired bowls with protein and vegetables</li>
                    <li><strong>Sandwiches:</strong> Gourmet sandwiches with fresh ingredients</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="menu-section">
                  <h3>üç∞ Desserts Under $10</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li><strong>Tiramisu:</strong> Classic Italian dessert</li>
                    <li><strong>Chocolate Cake:</strong> Rich and indulgent</li>
                    <li><strong>Ice Cream:</strong> Artisanal flavors and sundaes</li>
                    <li><strong>Fruit Tarts:</strong> Fresh and light options</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="conclusion">
              <h2>Romantic Date Nights on Any Budget</h2>
              <p>Creating memorable date nights doesn't require spending a fortune. Los Angeles offers countless budget-friendly restaurants that provide excellent food, romantic ambiance, and unique experiences without breaking the bank.</p>
              
              <p>By being strategic about timing, sharing dishes, and exploring different neighborhoods and cuisines, you can enjoy incredible date nights while staying within your budget. The key is focusing on the experience and connection rather than the price tag.</p>
            </section>
          </div>
          
          <aside class="sidebar">
            <div class="related-posts">
